Giulia is a 6 years old girl, born in Bologna who loves bedtime stories with her father Emilio. Giulia is curious and bold and always wants to try new experiences, one day she comes home after school and insists on wanting to go outside even though it's raining, so her dad... [[...looks online to find some inspirations for inside activities in the city]] [[...turns on the tv and tells her they will go out the day after]]Double-click this passage to edit it.Sad to see you go! Are you sure you don't want to give it another try? [[Restart->He is intrigued and follows the pop-up...]]The advertisments advises: "A new gamification experience is taking over right in the heart of Bologna. A greek hero is looking for brave kids to help him save his land and take back his throne from an evil king. He has been sent on a quest to find a well protected treasure and on his journey he will fight storms, giants and mythical creatures with the help of loyal friends and powerful witches. Discover a new entertaining way to admire Carracci's frescoes in Palazzo Fava with your children!" [[Emilio close the ad and look for something else]] [[Emilio gets caught up in the ad and decide to try the experience with his daughter]] Emilio takes Giulia to Palazzo Fava, happy to see it is located in a strategic position in the center of the city. They go inside and pay the entrance fee with the promotional discount for families wanting to try and test the new experience <!-- (how much?? per le mostre biglietto intero 15 più 10 per i bambini 6-11 anni wtf, in teoria alle sale vuote dovrebbe essere gratuito facciamo offerta promozionale 12€ tutto?) --> The attendant offers them a tablet and a set of haedphones and leave them to reach the room on the first floor. [[They take the devices and go upstairs...]]Arrived on the first floor they are guided towards the first room, they found it almost empty, with some paintings hung at the walls and signs on the ground that encourage them to look up, toward the ceiling where they see a cycle of interesting frescoes, but it's hard for them, and especially for Giulia to grasp their details. them, the nymphes of the sea have left some vases on the path containing all the tips she will need to deal with them, along with some curious place around Bologna where she could be able to recognize in statues and paintings those same creatures she will find in the labyrinth. Discover them all! [[Poseidon the God of the Sea]] [[Syrens]] [[Seahorses]] [[Exit the labyrinth!]]Poseidon is the God of the Sea, brother of Zeus, the most powerful amongst the greek gods, Poseidon protects sailors but beware of not make him mad! He could unleash a terrible storm and wreck your ship! The Romans called him Neptune and in the sixteenth century Giambologna portrayed him in a beautiful bronze statue. You've surely seen it before: it is located in the heart of Bologna, right next to Palazzo d'Accursio, a few minutes from Palazzo Fava. [[Keep looking!->Start playing]]On your long journey across the sea you may hear not only the sound of the waves or the seagulls screeching. Mermaids are creatures half women and half fish that usually sit on huge rocks singing beautiful songs or swim underwater with their friends, the newts. But beware! Many sailors chasing their voice, have collided with their rocks, sinking with their ships into the sea! In Bologna there are many statues depicting them: in addition to the fountain of Neptune, they were carved in other monuments. In 1888 Diego Sarti, for example, dedicated an opera to these fascinating creatures in the Montagnola park, near the station. [[Almost there! But you still have some secrets to discover!->Start playing]]It jumps between the waves, but it is not a dolphin: it is the hippocampus (yes, it is called just like seahorses!). Its name derives from ancient Greek and means "sea horse": it is in fact a horse with the tail and legs replaced by a large fin. They are faithful companions of Poseidon, the king of the sea, who rides them to travel among the oceans. They are gentle creatures and a beautiful fountain carved by Diego Sarti on the Scala della Montagnola in 1896 proves it. There, a brave hippocampus, in fact, tries to save a young nymph chased by a terrifying sea monster. [[Good job you now know all the secrets that the sea hides! You can safely exit the labyrinth!->Start playing]]"You solved the labyrinth! You're one step closer to get Jason to reclaim his throne! But the story is far from over! There are still numerous exciting adventures you will have to face, go to the second scene and find out what will happen to the Argonauts and how you can help them!" [[Keep playing!]]At this point the experience will continue with the same structure: a brief story told by Chirone while the animation of the correspondent frescoes' scene unfold on display, accompanied and spaced out by games, giving insights on the past of the epic cycle of the Argonauts while keeping an eye open for connection with other wonders hidden in Bologna. Emilio and Giulia take the map and exit the building, the sun is shining again and Emilio asks her daughter: "What do you want to do now?" However a pop up comes out on the website, advertising a new experience perfect for children 5-10 yo. [[1. Harpy]] [[2. Satyr]] [[3. Pegasus]] [[4. Dragon]]Great choice! Harpies are mythical creatures, women with the body of beautiful eagles and they were believed to have a perfect memory and used to protect the knowledge of the past! [[Next step!]]Great choice! Satyrs are mythical creatures, men with legs and horns of goats and they were believed to love music and dance, and had a great sense of humor. They also loved nature and were often consider as guardians of forests and woods! [[Next step!]]Great choice! Pegasus are mythical creatures, winged horses, sons of Poseidon the God of the Sea, they were loyal and powerful and often guides and helpers of greek heroes during their journeys and quests. [[Next step!]]Great choice! Dragons are mythical creatures with lizard-like bodies and majestic wings, they are powerful and strong and usually their role was to protect treasures and important objects or places. You will meet a dragon even during this story! [[Next step!]]
